Though, her rate of functions was much more quick them Prowls, her build to 
strike with speed and not with brawn, though everything slowed down when she 
had to resort to that.
< Noo!>

body as they began to mutate and expand, the exo-structire print of the

Slowly and painfully her armor seemed to split down the middle, light 
eminating from inside. And in a rush of speed and grinding of gears her

inner self.
SBM: < You failed!>
<...like always.>
Nothing worked out as she planned, ever. Either something was in the way, 
battle always interfeared, or people didn't follow commands.
It was deppressing, and she almost didn't remember what being happy felt 
like.
The instincts of the beast mode tried to take over, but the sinking feeling 
of disappointment kept it at bay, too thick to go through.
The feeling was very strong and she wouldn't be surprised if Prowl felt 
it...but it seemed everything she felt these days seemed to leave him 
uneffected, so this probably wouldn't be any different.*
